article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 73, Fla. International 70
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Landon Adler scored 23 points and Casey Wohlleb added 21 as Florida Gulf Coast beat Florida International 73-70 on Sunday. Adler also had 12 rebounds for Fla. Gulf Coast (3-5), and Adam Liddell finished with 13 points. Liddell and Wohlleb each pulled down four rebounds. The lead changed 18 times Sunday and the score was tied seven times. Erick Nsangou had 17 points for Fla. International (2-3), Kenneth White finished with 10 and Chris Fuller scored nine points. Alex Galindo and Russell Hicks each finished with eight points. Hicks also pulled down nine rebounds for Fla. International and Galindo had four.
